commit.message:
Build: migrate to pyproject.toml

setup.py is now legacy
Migrate to pyproject.toml

To simplify things, move the package to a src folder, which is the standard way to
organize a Python package (this might open the possibility to migrate the tests to pytest too, without sys.path insert hacks)

Drop Python 3.6 support due to:
https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/3269#issuecomment-1254507377
The pyproject.toml file we are shipping is not compatible with Pip 21.X, and Pip 22.X dropped support for Python 3.6
